medical_history.chief_complaint: The patient presents with ambiguous genitalia and skeletal dysplasia.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The patient's symptoms were noted at birth when external female genitalia appeared. The patient had moderate developmental delay, standing at 1 year of age and walking at 3 years of age after undergoing constant physiotherapy.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient had a cleft palate, corrected at 4 months of age, and has undergone constant physiotherapy for developmental delay.
